The view limits button allows you to see both the caution limits and the safe limits. If a value is within the caution limits then it will be marked as safe and so no warning will be displayed. However, if it is outside the caution limits then it will be either marked as caution or as danger. This is determined by if it also falls outside the safe limits (in which it will be marked as danger)."
